cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for image generation and weakly object localization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attention transfer mechanism, which falls under the category of transfer learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques for image generation and object localization, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with image data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of attention maps for data annotation, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
